				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, you definitely have to mind the ends of the table if you plan on having values wrapping around. Complete freedom will require you to have 2 tables back to back (512 bytes total) and use the lower table for adding and the upper table for subtracting.<br /><br />BTW, another advantage of a $00-$ff table is being able to perform operations between the accumulator and the index registers, such as ADC, SBC, AND, ORA, EOR... (e.g. A + X = ADC ByteTable, x).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

