				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You could also make the table smaller if you know your Y and X transfers in your TYX/TXY substitutes are always going to be smaller than the table size. Making macros out of TYX, TXY, and the table inclusion, you could set your assembler to output an error if the param exceeds the limit of the table size you've chosen.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
