			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A macro can have more uses than that. For example, you can set target platform in your config or at the top of main and your macros can adjust accordingly, automatically replacing a 6502 workaround with a more efficient 65816 opcode for you at assembly time without needing to search and replace. <br /><br />But yeah i agree, it's a balance. You shouldn't obfuscate code just for the sake of it. <br /><br />Macros not being in alphabetical order is a non-argument, though. Ctrl-F is always faster/more convenient than browsing.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
