					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Unless i'm missing something (again then), substituting an opcode from another processor, and autoreplacement based on conditional assembly are two different uses though (even if the latter must necessarily include the first). Like letting the macro conditionally select between branch always, and clc+bcs, or even just bcs if we know the carry flag is clear, based on what processor you have defined in your config. your if directives in the macro does the rest for you.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
